millsfield:images_texts:
Just bevond the southern horizon lies a
new world of travel wonders. Another con-
tinent. a different hemisphere. romantic
lands, friendly peoples, quaint customs, mu-
sical languages
-and scenic splendor un-
matched on the face of the globe. Cuba,
Jamaica, Colombia, Panama, Ecuador, Peru,
Chile. Picturesque lands, glamorous cities
names we have romanced with
cince
childhood but only dreamed of ever seeing.
Today, the magic of winged travel has
brought all of these within hours where they
were, only yesterday, days and weeks away.
And here, for the first time, is an ideal way
to visit these wonderlands. A "Cruise of
Discovery" through the lands of the Andes
to lovely, once far-off Chile! This remark-
able cruise takes you across the Caribbean
Sea to the southern continent, via Cuba and
Jamaica ... over the Spanish Main to the
Panama Canal . . . along South America's
kaleidoscopic west coast, through Colombia
and Ecuador to the Equator ... then down
the thirty-five hundred wonder-filled miles
along the base of the Andes to Chile's world
capital of Santiago ... home again through
the Land of the Incas, over Pizarro's his-
toric trail to Panama. Thence if you wish,
either
across the Caribbean
again or
through the tropic wonderlands of Central
America and the colorful
panorama of
Mexico. There are four itineraries to choose
from, each complete. How long? Within the
time limits of an ordinary
vacation__17
days. How far? 14,000 miles, through 38
cities in 14 countriesto the end of the
southern continent and back. How much?
The rates—including
all
expenses—are
amazingly low. How? No overnight trip
was ever easier to arrange for than this.
You have but to pack your bag—and go.
May we send you complete details and itin-
erary for this unique air cruise? We will
gladly
send them-without the slightest
obligation.
